<br>
Quick note.  I think we have proof beyond doubt that Celdor is a bard who is out to be the best he can be, for himself and for his guild.  And so, the usefulness of the bard epic is evident.  I think every bard who has the same goal will therefore be epic-fixated to unlock their potential.  And those who don't take it quite as seriously can and will, as Trech says, play the game without it.<br>
<br>
Shardon, I can only say that even though Naggy and Vox are child's play to you, they are a big deal to all the less equipped and powerful people who attend them.  And that being the case, however silly it may seem to you and however pragmatic one can be about the loot drops, it all falls short of the feeling these people get when they drop their first boss mob or go on their first multigroup raid.<br>
<br>
And that being said, I think one has to understand that to a little fish that has grown in the small pond of group XP for 45 levels, that first taste of a larger ocean is a huge deal to them.<br>
<br>
